# Implementation Plan: Site Entity for CMMS Platform

## Problem

The CMMS platform currently has no **Site** entity. In a real-world CMMS system:
- Every **Organization** has multiple **Sites** (physical locations/facilities).
- A **Facility Manager** is assigned to manage a site (1 FM → 1 Site).
- Each site has many **Technicians** working at it (one-to-many relationship: a technician belongs to exactly one site).
- Work orders, assets, and other entities should eventually be scoped to a site.

This plan adds the `Site` entity end-to-end following the existing architecture:  
**Route → Controller → Service → Repository → Model**

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Site Schema**: I'm assuming the following columns for `sites`. Please confirm or adjust:
> - `name` (required, unique per org), `address`, `city`, `state`, `zip_code`, `country`, `phone`, `description`, `is_active`
> - `manager_id` — FK to `users` (one FM per site, nullable)
> - `org_id` — FK to `organizations`

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Technician Assignment**: Per recent requirements, there is a **One-to-Many** relationship between Sites and Technicians. A `site_id` foreign key will be added directly to the `users` table, ensuring a technician belongs to exactly one site.

> [!WARNING]
> **No cascading scope changes yet**: This plan adds the Site entity and CRUD. It does **not** re-scope existing entities (assets, work orders, inventory) to sites. That would be a larger follow-up change. Please confirm if you want those in scope now or later.

